author: @davidkosiba624

text:
‚Äã¬†@RyouEmerald¬† I don't need to be mad to say that the game isn't very good. It has lots of issues and really nothing that good to compensate for them. Characters are mentally retarded, Ethan has plain brain damage, the story is nonsensical and contrived for no good reason, the bosses are rushed and wasted in terms of potential, the enemies are sponges that just make the weapons feel weak, the werewolves and vampires are thematically non-entities and the Duke as a whole doesn't make any sense. It's only similar to 4 in a shallow way and is just poorly made as a whole.
People are quite free to like it and enjoy it to their hearts' content, but using that as a base for saying that "it's good" while ignoring its issues is just the laziest and most hollow praise you can give to something.
author: @VladDascaliuc

text:
¬†@davidkosiba624¬† Why would I need to be mad to say what I said? And how would being mad invalidate it, anyways? This is just being dismissive for the sake of it. Nobody is attacking your preferences, so no need for that. 
As for you saying that I shouldn't call the game bad, I would just explain to you why I'm saying that it is and I would provide you references and explanations for each case. The game is fun, but it's disingenuous to say it's well made in the slightest. "I like it" and "It's good" are completely different, and people need to stop equating them all the time. It being an opinion does not stop it from being wrong. 
Though if you considered this "game of the year" then I would really put into question your standards.
author: @VladDascaliuc

text:
¬†@VladDascaliuc¬† There are parts I like and parts I'm not so fond of in this game. We just need to give it the credits where it's due. Just put in some compliments in between, and people would be more receptive to your criticism.

Personally, I think the franchise's writing is in a weird place for some time since it moved from a local scale to a worldwide scale, so I don't have that much expectation of it regarding the plausibility.
author: @chaoton

text: ¬†@VladDascaliuc¬† i like the story , general appeal of characters and setting , music , it's not like re 5 or 6 , the gameplay is ok . Could be longer yea but whatever , re 3 remake was only 5H while r8 is like 10h
author: @theteamxxx3142

text:
‚Äã¬†@VladDascaliuc¬† A game should be fun to play first and foremost and this game is.  If you are playing RE games for the plot you are in the minority....they have been dumb soap operas with monsters for a long time. 

A game having issues doesn't immediately make it objectively bad.  I would consider Morrowind to be one of the best games of all time and it's janky as all hell.
author: @OriginalDad

text: ¬†@theteamxxx3142¬† What do you like of the story? And what do you mean by "general appeal of characters and setting"?
author: @VladDascaliuc

text:
¬†@OriginalDad¬† Any game can be fun, regardless of how good or bad they are. There are some games that are so bad that they aren't fun at all and there are also games that very good but that you wouldn't call "fun", strictly speaking. Saying that this game is fun, albeit mostly true, doesn't say anything about its actual quality, and as such I don't see a point in anyone trying to bring that up as a rebutal. 
It's not that it's bad because it has some issues. It's pretty bad because it has issues at almost every single level other than maybe graphics while not having pretty much anything to make up for it. Everything is dumb, and I don't think you realize what that actually entails.  
And come on, the "it has always been bad" is a weak and lazy excuse. Please never use that anywhere again. It just doesn't work.
